# set(_:forKey:)

**Instance Method**

Sets the value of the specified key to a dictionary of property list objects.

## Declaration

```swift
func set(_ aDictionary: [String : Any]?, forKey aKey: String)
```

## Parameters

- **aDictionary**: The dictionary object to save in the iCloud key-value store. The dictionary must contain only property list types.
- **aKey**: The key to associate with the value.

## Setting values

- **set(_:forKey:)**: Sets the value of the specified key to a Boolean value.
- **set(_:forKey:)**: Sets the value of the specified key to a double value.
- **set(_:forKey:)**: Sets the value of the specified key to a 64-bit integer value.
- **set(_:forKey:)**: Sets the value of the specified key to a string value.
- **set(_:forKey:)**: Sets the value of the specified key to a data object.
- **set(_:forKey:)**: Sets the value of the specified key to a property list object.
- **set(_:forKey:)**: Sets the value of the specified key to an array of property list objects.
